=begin pod
=head1 Enumerations

=head2 GtkFileChooserAction

Describes whether a U<Gnome::Gtk4::R-FileChooser> is being used to open existing files
or to save to a possibly new file.
=item C<GTK_FILE_CHOOSER_ACTION_OPEN>; Indicates open mode.  The file chooser
 will only let the user pick an existing file.
=item C<GTK_FILE_CHOOSER_ACTION_SAVE>; Indicates save mode.  The file chooser
 will let the user pick an existing file, or type in a new
 filename.
=item C<GTK_FILE_CHOOSER_ACTION_SELECT_FOLDER>; Indicates an Open mode for
 selecting folders.  The file chooser will let the user pick an
 existing folder.

=head2 GtkFileChooserError

These identify the various errors that can occur while calling
U<Gnome::Gtk4::R-FileChooser> functions.
=item C<GTK_FILE_CHOOSER_ERROR_NONEXISTENT>; Indicates that a file does not exist.
=item C<GTK_FILE_CHOOSER_ERROR_BAD_FILENAME>; Indicates a malformed filename.
=item C<GTK_FILE_CHOOSER_ERROR_ALREADY_EXISTS>; Indicates a duplicate path (e.g. when
 adding a bookmark).
=item C<GTK_FILE_CHOOSER_ERROR_INCOMPLETE_HOSTNAME>; Indicates an incomplete hostname
 (e.g. "http://foo" without a slash after that).
=end pod

